        "creation_date": 1602142437,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Convert java function with long variable to NodeJS",
        "body": "<p>In Java function have &quot;long&quot; variable.<\/p>\n<pre><code>public class LongToIntExample1{  \n    public static void main(String args[]){  \n        long l=2672558412L;  \n        int i=(int)l;  \n        System.out.println(i);  \n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>=&gt; Output: -1622408884<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>I tried with NodeJS function as below but wrong output:<\/p>\n<pre><code>module.exports.LongToIntExample1 = () =&gt; {\n    var l = 2672558412n;\n    var i = parseInt(l);\n    console.log(i);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>=&gt; Output: 2672558412<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>How to write NodeJS function as Java function with same output?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 64257800,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "node.js",
            "long-integer"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 64258152,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 215
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/06e1c4b46656313883eda6e96e9ab4e9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1912441,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1725871,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1725871/josste",
