            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1602186721,
            "creation_date": 1602143313,
            "body": "<p>If you read this answer: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/4355475/1725871\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/4355475/1725871<\/a> Java will wrap the part of the <code>long<\/code> that is over <code>Integer.MAX_VALUE<\/code> around and the value will become negative.<\/p>\n<p>Clearly that is not the case in NodeJS<\/p>\n<p>Since a long is bigger than an int, the behaviour you are trying to reproduce is actually a biproduct of the Java implementation not being safe, ie not checking if the long value is less than <code>Integer.MAX_VALUE<\/code><\/p>\n<p>Personally I would not rely on a mechanic like that in my programs<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 64258025,
            "question_id": 64257800,
            "last_edit_date": 1602186721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/ZpIj6.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 9762590,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7237224,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7237224/terry-lennox",
                "reputation": 30915,
                "display_name": "Terry Lennox"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1602144246,
            "creation_date": 1602143793,
            "body": "<p>We can cast the number to a 32-bit signed int, using the built-in <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Int32Array\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Int32Array<\/a> like so:<\/p>\n<p><div class=\"snippet\" data-lang=\"js\" data-hide=\"false\" data-console=\"true\" data-babel=\"false\">\r\n<div class=\"snippet-code\">\r\n<pre class=\"snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override\"><code>function LongToIntExample1(num) {\n     return (new Int32Array([num]))[0];\n}\n \nconsole.log(LongToIntExample1(2672558412))\nconsole.log(LongToIntExample1(2147483647))<\/code><\/pre>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 64258152,
